<h1>Trust component demonstration</h1>

<p class="lede">This is a component demonstration, not content. It exists to prove the trust component renders a fact correctly and to serve as an accessibility target. The fact below is a fixture with no verification passes, so the component withholds its value rather than asserting it.</p>

<p>For a withheld fact the component shows a plain "not yet verified" state and, behind a disclosure you can open, the sources being checked and the last-updated date. Once a fact meets the standard its claim type demands, the same component instead shows the value with two inline text tokens for confidence and evidence, each a link to the part of the methodology that defines it.</p>

